createMeasurementConfigurationAddon

MeasurementPostProcessorAddon createMeasurementConfigurationAddon(java.lang.String ID,
                                                                  YouScopeClientConnection client,
                                                                  YouScopeServer server,
                                                                  java.lang.String measurementFolder)
Returns a new post-processing addon for the given ID, or null if addon does not support the post-processing with the given ID.

Parameters:
ID - The ID for which a post-processor should be created.
client - Interface to allow the addon to communicate with the client.
server - Interface to the server.
measurementFolder - The folder where the measurement is saved.
Returns:
The created addon to configure a measurement.

getSupportedPostProcessorIDs

java.lang.String[] getSupportedPostProcessorIDs()
Returns a list of all measurement post-processor types supported by this addon.

Returns:
List of supported post-processors.

supportsPostProcessorID

boolean supportsPostProcessorID(java.lang.String ID)
Returns true if this addon supports post-processors with the given ID, false otherwise.

Parameters:
ID - The ID of the measurement post-processor for which it should be queried if this addon supports its construction.
Returns:
True if this addon supports post-processors with the given ID, false otherwise.

getPostProcessorName

java.lang.String getPostProcessorName(java.lang.String ID)
Should return a short human readable name of the post-processor which corresponds to the given ID. If the addon does not support the post-processor with the given ID, null should be returned.

Parameters:
ID - The ID of the post-processor for which the human readable name should be returned.
Returns:
Human readable name of the post-processor.
